  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An uncontrolled feasibility study on using mouth piece ventilation in palliation of dyspnea
      in subjects with incurable advanced disease. Subjects are recruited from a local Hospice and
      from oncology ward. The main outcomes are the compliance of the subjects with the treatment
      and alleviation of dyspnea during the treatment period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
